ld acknowledge the innovative contributions of the avant-garde. The anthology, which presents examples of French and Russian Symbolism, Italian Futurism, German Expression-ism, and Dada-Surrealism, as well as work by such seminal figures as Jarry, Strindberg, Artaud, and Kandinsky, illuminates the astonishing daring of these writers from many Western countries and diverse theatrical movements.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aDramax20th century. 0aDramay20th century. 0aExperimental dramaxHistory and criticism. 0aThéâtre (Genre littéraire)xHistoire et critiquex20e siècle. 0aThéâtre expérimentalxHistoire et critique. 7aDRAMA / Anthologies (multiple authors).2bisacsh1 aCardullo, Bert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aKnopf, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYUP eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066772108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300133042423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780300133042.jpg  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press eBook Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  a978-3-11-066772-1  YUP eBook-Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles